----------FILE-MANAGEMENT------------

----PERMISSIONS----

-rw-r--r--  1 shelby shelby   16 Dec 16 16:58 file
- READ(1) WRITE(2) EXECUTE(6) NONE(0)
- OWNER GROUP OTHERS 

ls -la : see file permission info
chmod 666 <file> : change file permissions
chmod +x <file> : chnage file permissions
chown <user> <file> : change ownership of file

----COMPRESSION-ARCHIVING----

tar -cvd <file>.tar <file> : archive a file
gzip <file>.tar : compress using gzip algo
tar -czvf <file>.tar.gz <file> : one way cmd for gzip compression
zip -r <file>.zip <file> : compress tpo zip format 

tar -tvf <file>.tar : see the contents without extraction
tar -tzvf <file>.tar.gz : see the contents of gzip file

tar -xvf <file>.tar -C <ext-dir> : extract the contents in the location
tar -xzvf <file>.tar.gz -C <ext-dir> : extract a gzip file
unzip -d <ext-dir> <file>.zip : extract from zip format

----HARD-SOFT-LINKS----

- HARD-LINKS are only for files, not for directory
- SOFT-LINKS are useful for both files and directory

ln <exist> <new> : create a HARD-LINK
ln -s <exist> <new> : create a SOFT-LINK

